  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And the Germans who were worked on the airport saw that a lot of invalids coming from the front line, and this beating them made them more aggressive and more hostile to the Jewish workers.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the Germans knew that there was Jewish partisans.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When I said before the [?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "English ?] guy actually was a partisan.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the Jewish people were very careful to deal with anything.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the civilian population, the non-Jewish people, the Aryan side, stopped dealing with the Jewish or to supply them with food and so on.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And a lot of the Lithuanian population-- not the Jewish, outside the ghetto-- lived for Germany.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They volunteered to work in Germany.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In the ghetto, life was very bad.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And people felt there was no medication, there was no food.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And on the black market, we could still buy saccharine, means sweetener, flour, bacon, eggs, chickens.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And as I said, my cousin, she used to be a chicken smuggler.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Why she smuggled it to life, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Maybe she picked it up on the road.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] I remember, later on, I'll tell you about myself in Germany.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And people start to build bunkers in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "As I mentioned before, one bunker, this policemen didn't even know his own wife and child was in the bunker, because people didn't discuss anything between themselves unless it was maybe very close family.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And this was not a single case, not one case, it was several cases.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "The Jewish police, or Jewish firemen, showed the Germans where the hiders are.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the Jewish people, in 1943, start to build better bunkers, more sophisticated, and they installed air ventilation pipes, and food supplies, and water supplies, if possible.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
